##############################################

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGML.pl",
  "PCCmacros.pl",
  "contextFiniteSolutionSets.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl",
);



##############################################


Context("Numeric");
Context()->noreduce("(-x)-y","(-x)+y");
$fname = RandomVariableName(type=>function);
Context()->strings->add("no real solutions"=>{},
  "no real solution"=>{alias=>'no real solutions'}, 
  "none"=>{alias=>'no real solutions'}, 
  );

do {
   $a = non_zero_random(-10,10,1);
   $b = non_zero_random(-10,10,1);
} until (abs($a)!=abs($b));
$sum = $a+$b;
$product = $a*$b;
$y1 = non_zero_random(-10,10,1);
$c = $product+$y1;

$func = Compute("x**2+$sum*x+$c")->reduce;

$s1 = Compute("x**2+$sum*x+$product")->reduce;
$s2 = Compute("(x+$a)(x+$b)")->reduce;

Context("FiniteSolutionSets");
$na = -$a;
$nb = -$b;
$ans = Formula("{$na,$nb}");


##############################################

TEXT(beginproblem());

BEGIN_PGML

Solve for [`x`], where [`[$fname](x)=[$func]`].

[@KeyboardInstructions('If there is no real solution, type no [|real solution|]*.')@]**

[`[$fname](x)=[$y1]`]  
[____________]{$ans}

END_PGML


##############################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

To solve for [`x`] for a given function value, we substitute [`[$fname](x)`] with [`[$func]`]:

    [``\begin{aligned}[t]
   [$fname](x) &= [$y1] \\
   [$func] &= [$y1] \\
   [$func] \mathbf{{}-[$y1]} &= [$y1] \mathbf{{}-[$y1]} \\
   [$s1] &= 0 \\
   [$s2] &= 0 \\
   x+[$a]=0 &\text{ or } x+[$b]=0 \\
   x=[$a*-1] &\text{ or } x=[$b*-1]
    \end{aligned}``]

If [`[$fname](x)=[$y1]`], then [`x=[$a*-1]`] or [`x=[$b*-1]`]. This implies [`[$fname]([$a*-1])=[$y1]`] and [`[$fname]([$b*-1])=[$y1]`].

END_PGML_SOLUTION


ENDDOCUMENT();

